mxGraph sharing server, running on Node.js, based on Sharejs (sharejs.org).

1 Development
-------------

For development, use the sharehost URL parameter as follows:

http://devhost.jgraph.com:8888/?sharehost=dev or
http://devhost.jgraph.com:8888/?sharehost=devhost.jgraph.com:8000

Where the latter can use any URL without the http prefix. For the sharing the
client will add /sjs or /dummy.gif to check if the server is up and running.

2. Installation
---------------

Put this directory under the node_modules directory, ie.

Windows: c:\users\username\AppData\Roaming\npm\node_modules
Linux: /usr/local/lib/node_modules or /usr/lib/node_modules

Then execute "npm install ./" inside the directory to install
the required dependencies or run the install task in build.xml.

3. Start
--------

On shr.diagramly.com, "cd /usr/lib/node_modules/mxshare" and use "node
bin/sharingserver &" to start the server, or the run task in build.xml.